                        <li> Creating a Well-Formed, Valid Document</li>
                            <ol type="1">
                                <dl>
                                    <li><dt>Your home page should be well formed, valid web page under either transitional, strict XHTML DTD or HTML5.</dt></li>
                                    <dd>The home page is valid under HTML5(Experimental) by W3Schools. At this time there is no icon to display when your webpage is well formed. To check please insert the "home.html" file into the <a href="https://validator.w3.org/#validate_by_uri+with_options">validation site</a> using the HTML(Experimental) option</dd>
                                </dl>
                            </ol>
                        <li> JavaScript Minimum Required Features</li>
                            <ol type="1">
                                <dl>
                                    <li><dt>Use of variables, arithmetic, comparison and logical operators, subroutines, functions, array, conditional statements, conditional operators, running time commands.</dt></li>
								    <dd>All of these JavaScript features are used in the validation file <a href="js/formValidate.js"> formValidate.js. </a></dd><br >
                                    
								    <li><dt>Display system date on the home page of the web site.</dt></li>
								    <dd>Each page(excluding the enter page) has a script function in the &lt;header&gt; that displays the system date. <a href="home.html"> View source to see. </a></dd><br />
                                    
								    <li><dt>Validating form input by using appropriate JavaScript functions.</dt></li>
								    <dd>See the validation function in <a href="js/formValidate.js"> formValidate.js</a></dd><br />
                                    
								    <li><dt>Use of JavaScript alerts for validation purposes.</dt></li>
								    <dd>See the validation function <a href="js/formValidate.js"> formValidate.js</a>. There are three instances of JavaScript alerts. Two during validation and one on submit.</dd><br />

